  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated a willingness to make restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the relatively modest amount of $25,000 paired with a clean criminal record suggests that a rehabilitative sentence is more appropriate than the harsh penalty suggested by the disruptive spectator. Imposing a 6-month period of incarceration provides sufficient accountability for the breach of trust while acknowledging the mitigating factors of the defendant's background and prior record.",
